The paper focuses on using deep learning models for automated calcium imaging segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of fully convolutional networks, which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the evaluation of different models, which is a common topic in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) research. Finally, the paper mentions the use of summary images and the speed of the model, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
